 "description": "Malte Per Wilhelm Gustaf Eurenius was born on August 8th, 1901 in Karlshamn, Sweden to court engraver Wilhelm G.D.E. Eurenius and Ebba Loven. He was an editor and had a particular interest in personal historical research. He was married to elementary school teacher Märta Kloo and they had two children, Lars and Margareta. Eurenius was a member of various associations and boards including Publicistklubben, Swedish Journalist Association, Karlskrona Rotary Club, Karlskrona City Library Board, Blekinge Museum and Heritage Association Board, and Nordic Association in Karlskrona Board."
